        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>119 E 72nd St<lb/>
                New York May 12&#47; 90<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr. S Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Rev Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr. Chapin has just<lb/> telegraphed me of Mr Belisario&#39;s<lb/> death at 5.50. P. M.  I suppose<lb/> you have also been acquainted&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have written to Dr Chapin<lb/> to hold the remains subject to<lb/> such directions as you may give&#44;<lb/> &#38; must now ask of you the service<lb/> I am unable to perform<lb/></p>
            <p>I have determined that<lb/> the interment had best be in<lb/> your city &#38; have to request<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>your kind offices to the end<lb/> that all arrangements may be<lb/> made against my arrival at<lb/> noon on the 14th.<lb/></p>
            <p>Permit me to authorize<lb/> your making every expense<lb/> necessary to ensure the poor consolation<lb/> to a mother&#44; of having provided<lb/> an appropriate resting place for<lb/> her son.<lb/></p>
            <p>Sincerely Yours<lb/> D H Brandon<lb/></p>
            <p>P. S.<lb/> Have just recd your wire<lb/> &#38; thank you for your proptness<sic></sic>.<lb/>  If you will write me where I<lb/> will meet the body&#45;&#45;it may<lb/> save me calling at Asylum.<lb/>  Yours &#38;c<lb/> D H B<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
